  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>lemongrass</strong>, <strong>basmati rice</strong> and 300ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once cooked, remove from the heat and keep covered until serving</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1598262414904-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1598262414904-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1598262414904-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1598262414904-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1598262414904-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, boil half a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely chop the <strong>shallot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Chop the<strong> green beans</strong> into bite-sized pieces</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1598262422502-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1598262422502-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1598262422502-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1598262422502-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1598262422502-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel the <strong>ginger</strong> and <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Slice the <strong>red chilli<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></strong> in half and scrape the seeds out with a spoon</p><p>Chop the <strong>coriander</strong> roughly, reserving some leaves for garnish</p><p>Add the<strong> ginger</strong>,<strong> garlic</strong>,<strong> half </strong>of<strong> </strong>the <strong>red chilli</strong> (save the rest for later) and <strong>chopped coriander</strong> to a <strong>food processor</strong> with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>water</strong> and blitz until smooth – this is your <strong>Thai green curry paste</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1602153376533-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
